# VCS-driven HCP Terraform ingests the WHOLE repository from the repo root and
# reads .terraformignore from HERE. (infra/.terraformignore only governs
# CLI-driven runs, where the package root is infra/ — it is inert for VCS runs.)
#
# This is a monorepo and the Terraform config is self-contained in infra/, so
# ship only that: keep the app source (portal/, runner/, web), the agent/dev
# dirs, CI, and docs out of the uploaded configuration version. Git-ignored
# local artifacts (.terraform/, terraform.tfvars, *.tfstate) are already absent
# from VCS ingestion, but excluding everything-but-infra is the durable guard.
/*
!/infra
